text: The National Network of Abortion Funds (NNAF) is an American non-profit organization. It was created to increase access to abortion for low-income people across the United States. In 2000, the Fund led the Campaign for Access to Reproductive Equity, which was meant to reverse the Hyde Amendment and make it possible for people to get Medicaid funding for abortions. ==References== Category:1993 establishments in the United States Category:Abortion in the United States
